tags: wow that took a long time to write
I’m kinda proud of it tho
summary: Spider-Man but he goes to children’s hospitals and lets them use the web shooters
question: Spider-Man but he goes to children’s hospitals and lets them use the web shooters
answer:
Peter didn’t think anyone would wanna see him, especially after everything the papers had said about him, until one day when Tony told him he had gotten a letter at the compound.
It was a letter from a little girl who was at the children’s hospital
“Dear Spiderman,
You’re really cool!! When I get out of here I’m gonna help you fight crime as spider girl!!!”
Then there was a drawing of him and a smaller pink Spiderman swinging around
“From Olive, age 7”
(It also had a ps that said My mom calls you a trouble maker but I think you’re just doing your best)
Peter remembered when he was little and saw Tony Stark in his iron man suit and how much it changed his life and he decided he was gonna go over there to say hi to Olive. (After he finished his homework of course)
As he walked in he started thinking maybe he shouldn’t have come when he heard someone yell “SPIDERMAN!!!”
A little girl on crutches rushed over to him followed by more and more kids
He had a great time showing all the kids how to use his web shooters and talking about how he developed the formula. He also signed about 100 papers.
Eventually he found Olives room. The nurse explained she wanted to come see him out in the hallway but at the moment she couldn’t get out of bed, none the less she was ecstatic to see him. They hung out and talked about fighting crime for a good hour and a half.
When he was about to leave she asked “hey Spiderman? Can I see under your mask?”
He was hesitant at first but then remembered what it was like to be a little kid seeing their favorite superhero for the first time, so he kneeled next to her bed lifted up his mask gave her a wink and said “Don’t tell the press okay?”
She giggled and smiled wider than he had seen anyone smile before.
After that day Peter didn’t stop smiling for about a week and he made sure to go visit Children’s hospitals at least a once a month.
